In 2023, audit firms @NethermindEth & @LeastAuthority conducted two separate security audits of the Worldcoin protocol. The audits covered the following areas:

‚Ä¢ Correctness of the implementation, including cryptographic constructions and primitives and appropriate use of smart contract constructs
‚Ä¢ Common and case-specific implementation errors
‚Ä¢ Adversarial actions and other attacks on the code
‚Ä¢ Secure key storage and proper management of encryption and signing keys
‚Ä¢ Exposure of any critical information during user interactions
‚Ä¢ Resistance to DDoS (distributed denial of service) and similar attacks
‚Ä¢ Vulnerabilities in the code leading to adversarial actions and other attacks
‚Ä¢ Protection against malicious attacks and other methods of exploitation
‚Ä¢ Performance problems or other potential impacts on performance
‚Ä¢ Data privacy, data leaking and information integrity
‚Ä¢ Inappropriate permissions, privilege escalation and excess authority

Authentication vs verification

Authenticating ownership (e.g. FaceID) uses biometrics as a password, where a 1:1 comparison is performed against a saved ID template.

Verifying uniqueness compares biometrics against (up to) billions of registered users in a 1:N comparison. https://t.co/u2cfHkKFI9
